In its bid to keep in form pending the resumption of the league, Shooting Stars FC has accepted an international friendly tie with the Republic of Benin U20 National team, National Daily learnt .
The Secretary General of Federation of Benin Football, Rigobert Koutonin in a letter dated 16th July, has requested for a friendly from the management of the Shooting Stars for the junior Squirrels ‚Äù as part of preparations for the final qualifying round of 2018 TOTAL U20 NIGER CAN, and would prefer recently at the Lekan Salami Stadium, Adamasingba, Ibadan.
However, the club has replied the letter granting the request after due consultations with the appropriate authority and stakeholders.
